OL,6,FHancock, of Walnut Close, Waddington,
OL,7,Fadmitted obstructing a coroner by
OL,8,Fhelping Metson dispose of Ms Bramley's
OL,9,Fbody.
OL,11,FJudge Simon Hirst told Metson: "You
OL,12,Fwill receive a sentence of life
OL,13,Fimprisonment. What needs to be decided
OL,14,Fis the minimum tariff you will have to
OL,15,Fserve before you are eligible to go
OL,16,Fbefore the parole board."
